  "title": "Pointwise Difference of Functions",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $X\\subseteq\\mathbb{R}$ and let $f,g:X\\to\\mathbb{R}$. The\npointwise difference $f-g:X\\to\\mathbb{R}$ is the function defined by\n\\[\n (f-g)(x)=f(x)-g(x)\n \\qquad (x\\in X).\n\\]",
